This paper falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) as it proposes a new semantic-based approach for the evaluation of information retrieval systems. It also involves the use of ontologies, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the growth of new users on the web, which could be related to databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) for user behavior analysis.
